## #clock-cells

**Value type:** `<u32>`

The *#clock-cells* property defines the number of cells required to encode a clock specifier for this clock provider. A value of 0 means no additional specifier cells are needed (a single fixed clock). A value of 1 means one cell (the clock ID) follows the phandle in `clocks` references.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi — multi-clock provider */
gcc: clock-controller@100000 {
    compatible = "qcom,sm8550-gcc";
    #clock-cells = <1>;
};

/* Single fixed clock — #clock-cells = <0> */
clk_apb: clk_apb {
    compatible = "fixed-clock";
    #clock-cells = <0>;
    clock-frequency = <24000000>;
};
```
